Q10. (Theory) What is a .gitignore file? Write a .gitignore for an Arduino project that excludes compiled output files (.hex, .elf), OS-specific files (.DS_Store, Thumbs.db), and IDE config folders (.vscode/, build/). (2 marks)

A  .gitignore file tells Git which files and folders should be ignored and not tracked in a repository. It is commonly used to exclude compiled files, temporary files, operating system files, and IDE-specific configuration folders that are not required for the project source code.
.gitignore for an Arduino Project
# Compiled Arduino output files
*.hex
*.elf

# Build directory
build/

# IDE configuration
.vscode/

# macOS system files
.DS_Store

# Windows system files
Thumbs.db
